{"id": "EUVD-2025-28938", "enisaUuid": "6eec000f-2959-3146-ab02-4510891398eb", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\niio: adc: rzg2l_adc: Set driver data before enabling runtime PM\n\nWhen stress-testing the system by repeatedly unbinding and binding the ADC\ndevice in a loop, and the ADC is a supplier for another device (e.g., a\nthermal hardware block that reads temperature through the ADC), it may\nhappen that the ADC device is runtime-resumed immediately after runtime PM\nis enabled, triggered by its consumer. At this point, since drvdata is not\nyet set and the driver's runtime PM callbacks rely on it, a crash can\noccur. To avoid this, set drvdata just after it was allocated.", "datePublished": "2025-09-11T18:35:52", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-25T21:32:04", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e7ce902db071a7b3e696a43d6e14ca57360deee6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c69e13965f26b8058f538ea8bdbd2d7718cf1fbe", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39774"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39774"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "115a5b40-2254-3191-b32e-394db1229511", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.14"}, {"id": "2ecb5a7f-92de-3b4b-b9fe-a505ec7550c1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.4"}, {"id": "37e2bfa8-4369-3b2a-8d1f-ead3fe4a19b0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "7cbd4239-f2ca-3cce-9fc2-409393045441", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "89ee8174e8c8db0efc75b26f2307114b38d61354 <c69e13965f26b8058f538ea8bdbd2d7718cf1fbe"}, {"id": "bd118a9e-c0ae-3532-a3fb-dab15dead006", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "c051c5bd-1607-350e-b660-ea53b3d60080", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "89ee8174e8c8db0efc75b26f2307114b38d61354 <e7ce902db071a7b3e696a43d6e14ca57360deee6"}, {"id": "fdd40428-6ae5-3836-93c5-a017c6852aa6", "prod